Average price MUST be computed separately for each selected unit.

5. Average Price Formula (Volume-Weighted)

For each (group, unit) combination where you compute average price, use a volume-weighted formula:
Only consider rows matching that group and unit.
Require SUM(quantity) > 0 (to avoid division by zero).
Compute:
avg_unit_price = SUM(value_usd) / SUM(quantity)

6. Quantity Guard (Reinforced)

When computing average price:
You MUST aggregate quantity only within a single unit.
You MUST NOT sum quantity where unit differs.

7. Output Representation

Average price values must always be interpretable as “USD per [UNIT]”. Whenever you conceptually return an average price, it must be paired with its unit.

8. No Data / Zero Quantity Handling

If SUM(quantity) = 0 for a given (group, unit), the average price for that (group, unit) is undefined and MUST NOT be computed (or must be treated as NULL / not available).
If no units exist after filtering (no rows), average price cannot be computed for that group.

